slxfig is a package that implements a number of S-Lang interpreter
routines that interface with fig2dev and LaTeX to produce publication
quality plots and drawings.

INSTALLATION:  Read the INSTALL file.

The examples/ subdirectory contains a number of scripts that
illustrate many of slxfig's features.

See <https://www.sternwarte.uni-erlangen.de/wiki/index.php/Plot_gallery>
for an impressive list of examples.

Visit <https://jedsoft.org/fun/slxfig/> for more information.
